President Muhammadu Buhari has lost his personal body guard, Warrant Officer (WO), Lawal Mato. He died yesterday after three years of battling  diabetes. Mato’s death was announced in a statement by presidential spokesman, Garba Shehu. The president described the officer, who had been working with him for many years before he won the 2015 presidential election, as “very thorough, trustworthy and dependable soldier who carried out his duty with diligence and focus.’’ Buhari prayed that Allah will ease his passage to paradise and grant his family, government and people of Jigawa State, the fortitude to bear the loss. Mato was part of a team that former President Umaru Musa Yar’Adua restored to President Buhari as personal security and he had been off full duty for three years, treating diabetes.  